{{Pre-columbian-stub}}

'''Vacuum cementing''' or '''vacuum welding''' is the natural process of solidifying small objects in a hard [[vacuum]]. The most notable example is [[Lunar dust|dust]] on the surface of the [[Moon]].
This effect was reported to be a problem with the first [[United States|American]] and [[Soviet Union|Soviet]] satellites, as small moving parts would seize together.{{citation needed|date=October 2010}}
In 2009 the [[European Space Agency]] published a peer-reviewed paper detailing why [[cold welding]] is a significant issue that [[spacecraft]] designers need to carefully consider. The conclusions of this appropriately titled study can be found on page 25 of "Assessment of Cold Welding between Separable Contact Surfaces due to Impact and Fretting under Vacuum". The paper also cites a documented example from 1991 with the [[Galileo spacecraft]] [[high-gain antenna]] (see page 2; the technical source document from [[NASA]] regarding the Galileo spacecraft is also provided in a link here).<ref>http://esmat.esa.int/Publications/Published_papers/STM-279.pdf</ref><ref>http://trs-new.jpl.nasa.gov/dspace/bitstream/2014/32404/1/94-0141.pdf</ref>
One source of difficulty is that vacuum (aka cold) welding does not exclude relative motion between the surfaces that are to be joined. This allows the broadly defined notions of [[galling]], [[fretting]], sticking, [[stiction]] and [[adhesion]] to overlap in some instances. For example, it is possible for a joint to be the result of both vacuum welding and galling (and/or fretting and/or impact). Galling and vacuum welding, therefore, are not mutually exclusive.
==See also== * [[Cold welding]] * [[Passivation (chemistry)|Passivation]] * [[Corrosion in space]]
== References == *[https://ntrs.nasa.gov/archive/nasa/casi.ntrs.nasa.gov/19650019853_1965019853.pdf The Implications of the Ranger Moon Pictures] (Page 4 references lunar dust vacuum welding) *[https://ntrs.nasa.gov/archive/nasa/casi.ntrs.nasa.gov/19900014421_1990014421.pdf Lunar Rated Fasteners] (Page 3 specifies how to build components resistant to vacuum welding) {{Reflist}}
{{DEFAULTSORT:Vacuum Cementing}}
[[Category:Spaceflight technologies]] [[Category:Vacuum]]
{{crater-stub}}
